    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>Q:</em> Bob began setting aside $5,000 per year in an equity fund at the age of 25. He has turned 30, and has just made another deposit into the fund. The fund has returned 4% annually. How much does Bob have in his account today?</p>

<p><em>A:</em></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;/p>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1>contribution at age&lt;/h1>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;blockquote>&lt;blockquote>&lt;blockquote>&lt;p>[(i, 5000)for i in range(25, 30+1)]
</span><span class='line'>[(25, 5000), (26, 5000), (27, 5000), (28, 5000), (29, 5000), (30, 5000)]&lt;/p>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p>sum([5000*pow(1.05, i-25) for i in range(25, 30+1)])
</span><span class='line'>34009.5640625</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote>
]]></content>
